attributes.text: Wow, I've got some work to do.  Did I mention I got a new job since the last update?
The Geohashing Wiki has moved!  As such, Geohash Droid now points there.

Okay, THIS time I've got the broken Version History entries fixed.  If you saw backslashed quotes show up in the previous version, that wasn't meant to be part of the joke; it turns out that, irritatingly, different versions of Android apparently parse single and double quotes in XML files differently.  Sorry for any confusion there.  Just remind me to always use ' and " to be safe and everything should be fine.
In the never-ending quest for fanciness and schmansiness, there's finally an adaptive-style icon for Geohash Droid.
A few minor bugs here and there should be fixed.  I have no clue if anyone ran across them or not.
A whoooooooole lotta code cleanup.  Library versions, linting, simplifying, the works.  If something exploded, do let me know.
There's still more to go, like fixing offline wiki post queueing and native Android 10 dark mode stuff.
